# ── Power BI Project (PBIP) ──
# Microsoft's exact baseline is **/.pbi/localSettings.json + **/.pbi/cache.abf.
# We deliberately ignore the WHOLE .pbi/ folder: every file under it is
# machine-local editor/workspace state (localSettings.json can carry connection
# context; cache.abf is the local data cache; editorSettings.json is local IDE
# state) -- none are model source. The model-as-code lives under definition/,
# which stays tracked. NEVER ignore definition/.
**/.pbi/

# ── Secrets ──
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# ── Python (future pipelines) ──
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.venv/
venv/
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# ── OS / editor junk ──
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
.idea/
.vscode/*
!.vscode/extensions.json

# ── Python build / test / lint caches ──
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/
*.egg-info/
.coverage
htmlcov/
dist/
build/
.mypy_cache/

# ── Vendored Power BI Modeling MCP (36MB binary tool, not source) ──
# The Microsoft Power BI Modeling MCP server, kept locally to build/edit the
# semantic model. It is a vendored binary, never committed (see .mcp.json for
# how Claude Code launches it).
*.vsix
tools/powerbi-modeling-mcp/
